observations.recommendation:
The Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Municipal Treasurer, submit the RIS and SSMI as supporting documents of the recorded expenses and make the necessary entries;

Set up the inventory accounts for every purchase of goods and other supplies and record the corresponding expense accounts only upon issuance and submission of the SSMI/RIS; and

Prepare necessary adjustments in the books of accounts to classify the items properly based on their characteristics based on the description of accounts in Annex B of COA Circular No. 2015-009.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to require:
the Municipal Accountant to coordinate with the GSO and Municipal Engineer in determining the correct total project cost for the construction of the approach wingwall and embankment in Calin-ay Poblacion and adjust the records accordingly;
the inventory committee to conduct a physical count of the 21 road networks specified in Appendix H to ensure their existence;
the concerned departments responsible for the recording of the road network of the Municipality to coordinate and establish a system to comply with the accounting and reporting requirements under COA Circular No. 2015-008; and
Inquire from the DILG Regional Office VII for the training schedules on LRAMs, and allow the concerned officials to attend, if available.

We recommended and Management agreed:
Direct the Municipal Agriculturist to conduct a physical count of all the biological assets taking into consideration their biological transformation and maintain and update the records for breeding stocks. Also, submit a report thereon to the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer so that the respective records of these offices can be updated and reconciled purposely to present fairly the accounts in the financial statements;
Require the Municipal Accountant to adjust the books of accounts to reflect the correct fair value of the biological assets based on the results of reconciliation and maintain WOABSLC for each type of breeding stock with sufficient details.
Justify the non-compliance with the 30-day period requirement to file the petition for relief from accountability;
Require the accountable officer the immediate submission of the petition for relief from accountability together with its complete supporting documents; or
Demand payment from the accountable officer for the value of dead animals, effect necessary adjusting entries after and submit proofs of payment and adjusting entries.
